#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""The `lore` CLI — vault scaffolding and section/status edit primitives.

Subcommands:
  lore init <path>          Scaffold a new vault (taxonomy + starter docs).
  lore new <type>           Render a template and write a new vault note.
  lore seed <name>          Scaffold an inbox capture + open it in Obsidian.
  lore patch <file> <sec>   Append text under a section (--text or stdin).
  lore set-status <f> <v>   Validate + set a note's frontmatter status.
  lore stats                Print counts for the resolved vault.
  lore session-note         Print this session's note path (id-first resolve).
  lore finish               Finalize the active session note for this worktree.
  lore handoff              Shelve the active session note for pickup later.
  lore shelved              List shelved/handoff session notes for pickup.
  lore resume [note|slug]   Flip a shelved/handoff note back to active
                            (omit the target to resume the current session).
  lore sync                 Stage, commit, and push the vault.
  lore review               Generate a vault migration-discipline report.
  lore validate             Check frontmatter against the canonical schema.

Finds its sibling ../scripts modules at import time so it works whether run
from the repo or from an installed plugin (${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/cli/lore).
"""
